modules/mysql/

modules/mysql/


Dependencies
============
* python-augeas
* python-sphinx
* python-netifaces, python-ipy (to log ip address)

Modules
-------
* Mysql
  apt-get install python-mysqldb

Client
------
* python-prettytable
* pip install argcomplete

Install All dependencies on Debian
----------------------------------
apt-get install python-augeas python-sphinx python-prettytable python-mysqldb python-netifaces python-ipy
pip install argcomplete


Install All dependencies on MBS
-------------------------------
1) Agent dependencies
   urpmi python-IPy python-netifaces python-pip python-mysql

2) Client dependencies
   urpmi git python-sphinx python-netifaces python-pip mysql python-mysql lib64selinux-devel
   pip install augeas
   pip install prettytable
   git clone https://github.com/giraldeau/python-augeas.git
   cd python-augeas/
   python setup.py install


Test Lifecycle and Augeas
=========================
cd mss/agent/classes/mss3
export PYTHONPATH=$PWD
mkdir /tmp/etc
cp -r /etc/mysql /tmp/etc/


Non interactive test
---------------------
python tests/tests_lifecycle.py

Interactive tests
-----------------
./client.py --help

Howto use bash completion
-------------------------
pip install argcomplete --user
Launch a new bash shell
eval "$(~/.local/bin/register-python-argcomplete  client.py)"


To get module documentation
---------------------------
python client-xmlrpc.py load Mysql
python client-xmlrpc.py dot Mysql > mysql.dot
dotty mysql.dot


To get full documentation
-------------------------
cd doc/
make html
firefox build/html/index.html


Ideas
=====
* Specify stability of states: unstable, exp, stable ...
  In order to manage community modules